{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2025-1850","published":"2025-07-18T14:49:20Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:31:28.281581Z","upstream":["CVE-2025-32023","CVE-2025-48367"],"summary":"redis security update","details":"Redis is an advanced key-value store. It is often referred to as a dattructure server since keys can contain strings, hashes ,lists, sets anorted sets.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nRedis is an open source, in-memory database that persists on disk. From 2.8 to before 8.0.3, 7.4.5, 7.2.10, and 6.2.19, an authenticated user may use a specially crafted string to trigger a stack/heap out of bounds write on hyperloglog operations, potentially leading to remote code execution. The bug likely affects all Redis versions with hyperloglog operations implemented. This vulnerability is fixed in 8.0.3, 7.4.5, 7.2.10, and 6.2.19. An additional workaround to mitigate the problem without patching the redis-server executable is to prevent users from executing hyperloglog operations. This can be done using ACL to restrict HLL commands.(CVE-2025-32023)\n\nRedis is an open source, in-memory database that persists on disk. An unauthenticated connection can cause repeated IP protocol errors, leading to client starvation and, ultimately, a denial of service. This vulnerability is fixed in 8.0.3, 7.4.5, 7.2.10, and 6.2.19.(CVE-2025-48367)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"redis","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS-SP2","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/redis&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"7.2.10-1.oe2403sp2"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["redis-7.2.10-1.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm","redis-debuginfo-7.2.10-1.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm","redis-debugsource-7.2.10-1.oe2403sp2.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["redis-7.2.10-1.oe2403sp2.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["redis-7.2.10-1.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm","redis-debuginfo-7.2.10-1.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm","redis-debugsource-7.2.10-1.oe2403sp2.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler